struct Point { x: i32, y: i32,
} impl std::ops::Add for Point { type Output = Self; fn add(self, other: Self) -> Self { Self { x: self.x + other.x, y: self.y + other.y } }
} fn main() { let p1 = Point { x: 10, y: 20 }; let p2 = Point { x: 100, y: 200 }; println!("{p1:?} + {p2:?} = {:?}", p1 + p2);
} 讨论点： You could implement Add for &Point. In which situations is that useful? 回答：Add:add 会耗用 self。如果您的运算符重载对象 （即类型 T）不是 Copy，建议您也为 &T 重载运算符。这可避免调用点上存在不必要的 克隆任务。 为什么 Output 是关联类型？可将它用作该方法的类型形参吗？ Short answer: Function type parameters are controlled by the caller, but associated types (like Output) are controlled by the implementer of a trait. 您可以针对两种不同类型实现 Add，例如， impl Add<(i32, i32)> for Point 会向 Point 中添加元组。 The Not trait (! operator) is notable because it does not "boolify" like the same operator in C-family languages; instead, for integer types it negates each bit of the number, which arithmetically is equivalent to subtracting it from -1: !5 == -6.

